hormone-secreting","Prolactin-secreting","Growth hormone-secreting","Non-functioning"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most common type of pituitary adenoma is the \u003Cstrong\u003Eprolactin-secreting adenoma\u003C/strong\u003E (prolactinoma), accounting for approximately 40% of all pituitary adenomas. \u003Cstrong\u003ENon-functioning adenomas\u003C/strong\u003E are the second most common type, comprising about 30% of cases. \u003Cstrong\u003EGrowth hormone-secreting adenomas\u003C/strong\u003E account for approximately 15% of cases, while \u003Cstrong\u003Eadrenocorticotropic hormone-secreting adenomas\u003C/strong\u003E represent about 10%. \u003Cstrong\u003EThyroid stimulating hormone-secreting adenomas\u003C/strong\u003E are rare, making up less than 1% of all pituitary adenomas.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Prolactinomas are the most common type of pituitary adenoma, accounting for approximately 40% of all cases.","Pituitary adenomas are classified based on their hormone production and cell of origin."],"references":["Fukuhara N, Nishiyama M, Iwasaki Y. Update in Pathogenesis, Diagnosis, and Therapy of Prolactinoma. Cancers (Basel). 2022 Jul 24;14(15):3604. doi: 10.3390/cancers14153604. PMID: 35892862; PMCID: PMC9331865.","Dai C, Kang J, Liu X, Yao Y, Wang H, Wang R. How to Classify and Define Pituitary Tumors: Recent Advances and Current Controversies. Front Endocrinol (Lausanne). 2021 Mar 17;12:604644. doi: 10.3389/fendo.2021.604644. PMID: 33815274; PMCID: PMC8010908.","Lenders NF, Earls PE, Inder WJ, McCormack AI. The evolution in pituitary tumour classification: a clinical perspective. Endocr Oncol. 2023 Apr 21;3(1):e220079. doi: 10.1530/EO-22-0079. PMID: 37434652; PMCID: PMC10305559.","Yatavelli RKR, Bhusal K. Prolactinoma. [Updated 2023 Jul 31]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih